title: Millburn High School girls volleyball team wins county tourney match
text:
Millburn High School girls volleyball team wins county tourney match October 21, 2015 Last updated: Wednesday, October 21, 2015, 3:44 PM By Jim Connelly Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly Iliana Sirkin (4), Miranda Nimmer (11) and Eva Raczkowski (13) of Millburn High School's varsity girls volleyball team celebrate after winning a point Oct. 16 in the first set of an Essex County Tournament preliminary round match against North 13th Street Tech. Teammate Angela Saggio is at back left. 
The outcome showed the 15th-seeded Millburn High School varsity girls volleyball team dispatched 18th-seeded North 13th Street Tech in two sets Oct. 16 in the preliminary round of the Essex County Tournament. 
Host Millburn jumped out to a 6-1 advantage on its way to winning the opening set in the best-of-three set match 25-16. Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly Millburn's Amy Nadel (pink shirt) sets up a shot Oct. 16 in the preliminary round of the Essex County Girls Volleyball Tournament. Looking on is teammate Miranda Nimmer. 
The second set was another story as the visitors won 12 of the set's first 17 points before the Millers rallied to pull out the set 25-19 and earn a first round match with second-seeded Montclair Kimberley Academy Saturday, Oct. 24, at 3 p.m. in Montclair. 
"We can't afford to play the way we did in the second set if we hope to win our division and be successful in the state tourney," Miller head coach Mikhail Sigalov said. 
Steady serves by senior Gillian Collas helped the Millers reel off six consecutive points, stretching their lead from 15-13 to 21-13. 
Collas recorded 13 service points, including three aces, in the match. She also recorded eight assists, tying her for tops on the team with junior Miranda Nimmer. 
Miller senior Eva Raczkowski recorded a team-high 12 digs. 
MILLER NOTES 
The triumph, Millburn's second of the season over its Super Essex Conference, Colonial Division rival, was the squad's third in a row after its campaign-opening 10-match winning streak came to an end Oct. 9 with a 2-0 loss to host Scotch Plains-Fanwood High School. 
The Millers entered this week's action with an 12-0 record in Colonial Division play, good for a one-game lead over Columbia High School (11-1) with two division matches left, including a contest set for Thursday, Oct. 22, at 4:30 p.m. at Columbia in Maplewood.
